	<exercise xml:id="class_work-pulling">
		<title>Doing Work</title>
		<p>
			
		</p>
		<p>
			You are pulling the box shown below from <m>x = 0</m> to <m>x = L</m>.  
			You find that as the box moves, the tension in the rope is not constant; 
			instead, it starts at <m>5T_0</m>, but by the time you reach <m>x = L</m> it has changed to <m>T_0</m>.  
			Assume the tension decreases linearly.
		</p>
