			<exercise>
				<title>Non-Constant Winch</title>
			<statement>
				<p>
					
				</p>
			  <p>You have a winch<fn>a machine that uses a rope to pull on another object</fn> that can be set to exert a changing force.  You decide to set your winch to produce the force <me>\vec{F}^{winch} = \frac{F_o}{L^2} (xL - x^2)\hat{x}</me> where <m>F_o</m> and <m>L</m> are constants and <m>x</m> is the position of the object being pulled.  Sketch a graph of this force vs. position and use it to find the work done by the winch between <m>x_i = 0</m> and <m>x_f = L</m>.</p>
				</statement>
				<answer>
				<p><me>W_{winch} = \frac{F_o L}{6}</me></p>
				</answer>
			</exercise>
			
